OL,3,CCarer and autistic man died in
OL,4,Cfreezing canal while out for a walk
OL,6,F"He knew that Aaron could not speak or
OL,7,Fswim. His focus would have been on
OL,8,Fhim, and not on himself."
OL,10,FThe jury was told Mr Jenkins, 60, had
OL,11,Fpreviously saved the life of a a
OL,12,Fstudent who had fallen into a canal
OL,13,Fwhen he worked at a high school in
OL,14,FWigan.
OL,16,FIn her statement Mrs Jenkins
OL,17,Fcontinued: "He was excellent at caring
OL,18,Ffor people. Ceri was always giving and
OL,19,Fcaring for other people. He always
OL,20,Ftook the time for others.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/11
