OL,3,CCarer and autistic man died in
OL,4,Cfreezing canal while out for a walk
OL,6,F"By getting to know them, he was able
OL,7,Fto help them."
OL,9,FThe jury heard that at 2.15pm on 28
OL,10,FNovember 2023, police logged calls
OL,11,Ffrom passers-by reporting two people
OL,12,Fin the canal. Emergency services
OL,13,Fattended, but both Mr Jenkins and Mr
OL,14,FRitchie died in hospital.
OL,16,FMr Ritchie's care needs had to be
OL,17,F"measured and monitored", the coroner
OL,18,Fsaid. The jury heard he enjoyed
OL,19,Fpicnics and going on walks to parks
OL,20,Fand along the canal - trips he would
OL,21,Fregularly take with his carers.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/11
