OL,3,CCarer and autistic man died in
OL,4,Cfreezing canal while out for a walk
OL,6,FShe said in a statement: "He was a
OL,7,Floveable rogue. He knew how to get his
OL,8,Fown way. He loved balls and laces - he
OL,9,Fused to hang them on the washing line."
OL,11,FShe said he seemed happy and content
OL,12,Fat Mayfield House, but had 'no sense
OL,13,Fof fear'.
OL,15,F"Aaron enjoyed going out with the
OL,16,Fstaff, going out on walks," Ms
OL,17,FDarbyshire added in the statement. "He
OL,18,Fparticularly liked going for walks
OL,19,Fdown the canal." She said there
OL,20,F'weren't many' warning signs that he
OL,21,Fwas about to have a seizure.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G9/11
