OL,3,CCarer and autistic man died in
OL,4,Cfreezing canal while out for a walk
OL,6,FMs Darbyshire said the canal walk they
OL,7,Fwere on was one of his favourites and
OL,8,Fhe had done it thousands of times. He
OL,9,Fcould not swim but was not "attracted"
OL,10,Fto open water.
OL,12,F"If he went in first, slipped or fell,
OL,13,FI don't know," she said. But she said
OL,14,Fthat if Mr Jenkins had gone into the
OL,15,Fwater first, Mr Ritchie would not have
OL,16,Fjumped in. He would have stayed on the
OL,17,Ftowpath, she added.
